Bruna Nessif is a creator, mystic, podcast host, speaker, writer, and author of Let That Shit Go: A Journey to Forgiveness, Healing & Understanding Love.

In 2020, Bruna began Return to Self, an educational resource & community that focuses on the journey of self-reflection & self-inquiry by accessing deeper awareness within the mind, body & soul.

She is a certified professional coach & Energy Leadership Index Master Practitioner from the Institute of Professional Excellence in Coaching, and an Usui/Holy Fire III Reiki Master. Her method of guidance is a hybrid of spiritual advisory & mindset coaching with the intention of helping people remember who they were before the world taught them who to be....read more

Spirit Song Singer & feminist folk punk musician, BloodSwan, f.k.a. RAINBOW STAR, glides out of the Appalachian foothills, where she tends her tiny house & homestead, in the Appalachian foothills.  
Swan is a powerful witch. In October 2020, Swan survived a preventative mastectomy, only to learn she had breast cancer (that was a close one!).  Eighteen months and six surgeries later, she came out on top, cancer free, and a wholly changed woman. "BloodSwan" is the graceful, resilient swim over a sea of one's own blood.
She is often accused of birthing strange, beautiful (and sometimes offensive), gloriously healing sonic spells. 
Fairy muses emerge from the forest to gift Swan her songs and poetry, as they have from the age of seven.  Swan is available for performances, witchy workshops, musician coaching, graphic design work for musicians, and hosts a sweet podcast, Musings from the Rainbow Sparkle Palace....read more
